body_html:
Is it possible that there is a version mismatch between the version of TensorFlow used to run the training script and the version of the library included in your Android application? (The exception message says "Check whether your GraphDef-interpreting binary is up to date with your GraphDef-generating binary").

The dilations attribute was added in commit cb4ef36#diff-632987400e5affbcdba4533444460b0e - so if the graph was generated with a version of TensorFlow with that commit but the Android library didn't contain that commit, then you'd see this error.

body:
Is it possible that there is a version mismatch between the version of TensorFlow used to run the training script and the version of the library included in your Android application? (The exception message says "Check whether your GraphDef-interpreting binary is up to date with your GraphDef-generating binary").

The `dilations` attribute was added in commit https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/commit/cb4ef362e4a18b3c42a2c90bdad8754d5ead4caf#diff-632987400e5affbcdba4533444460b0e - so if the graph was generated with a version of TensorFlow with that commit but the Android library didn't contain that commit, then you'd see this error.
